The paper introduces a novel approach to prognosis using neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper proposes a new recurrent neural network cell designed to merge physics-informed and data-driven layers, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper focuses on modeling the useful life of engineering assets, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
